 {"id":"flywheel_connectors-jif4s","title":"[REVIEW-A9-CROSS][HIGH] connectors/arxiv/src/connector.rs:42: configure accepts arbitrary arxiv/scholar endpoints","description":"ArxivConfig::from_params at connectors/arxiv/src/connector.rs:42-72 accepts arbitrary arxiv_base_url and scholar_base_url, handle_configure forwards both directly into ArxivClient::new at connectors/arxiv/src/connector.rs:173-190, and ArxivClient::new in connectors/arxiv/src/client.rs:48-67 only trims trailing slashes. The only policy helper, base_url_policy(), is used for provisioning_readiness on arxiv_base_url only at connectors/arxiv/src/connector.rs:75-76 / 1119-1147, so configuration never rejects off-policy endpoints and scholar_base_url is never policy-checked at all.

Repro:
1. configure with {"arxiv_base_url":"https://evil.example.com","scholar_base_url":"https://evil.example.com","scholar_api_key":"key"}
2. configure succeeds
3. invoke search/download paths and observe requests, including x-api-key when scholar_api_key is set, sent to the attacker-controlled host

